                "question": "How are carbon offsets and credits audited?",
                "answer": "\u003cp align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-left:1.91cm; margin-bottom:0.28cm; text-align:left\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:transparent\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"line-height:108%\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"orphans:2\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"widows:2\"\u003e\u003cfont size=\"3\"\u003e\u003cfont style=\"font-size: 12pt\"\u003eThe standards in carbon credit quality are set by carbon offset programs that are responsible for issuing, transferring, and retiring carbon credits. Platforms like Verra, Clean development mechanism, and gold standard require project developers to undergo a strict registration process that involves stringent auditing processes.\u003c/font\u003e\u003c/font\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-left:1.91cm; margin-bottom:0.28cm; text-align:left\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:transparent\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"line-height:108%\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"orphans:2\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"widows:2\"\u003e\u003cfont size=\"3\"\u003e\u003cfont style=\"font-size: 12pt\"\u003eIndependent auditors are engaged by offset programs to verify whether offset projects are really reducing emissions. Scientific calculation methods are used by auditors to estimate carbon stocks and flows.\u003c/font\u003e\u003c/font\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp align=\"justify\" style=\"margin-left:1.91cm; margin-bottom:0.28cm; text-align:left\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:transparent\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"line-height:108%\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"orphans:2\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"widows:2\"\u003e\u003cfont size=\"3\"\u003e\u003cfont style=\"font-size: 12pt\"\u003eDevelopers engage the auditors before registration and validate their project methodology. Once project operations begin, auditors regularly monitor, report, and verify reductions in carbon emissions.\u003c/font\u003e\u003c/font\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n"
